    "id": 202601,
    "firstName": "Brianna",
    "lastName": "Cetta",
    "projectTitle": "Demonstrating SDN-Based Attack Isolation and Response in a Mininet VM",
    "projectDesc": "This capstone project utilizes the Mininet emulation platform and the OpenFlow protocol to demonstrate the effectiveness of Software-Defined Networking (SDN) in isolating cyber threats. By centralizing network intelligence, the project addresses the limitations of traditional hardware-based defenses, which often cause collateral damage to legitimate traffic during mitigation. The implementation was executed in two core phases: Phase 1 focused on the deployment of a virtualized network and the simulation of a high-volume UDP flood attack, while Phase 2 utilized real-time telemetry and manual flow-rule injection to neutralize the attack at the source switch. The results validate that a software-driven approach provides the fine-grained control necessary to preserve network availability for innocent users while maintaining a robust defensive posture against volumetric threats.",
    "keywords": "Mininet, OpenFlow, Software-Defined Networking (SDN)",
